---
interface Props {
	showMiniHeading?: boolean;
}

const { showMiniHeading = false }: Props = Astro.props;
---

<div class="content">
  {showMiniHeading && <h3 class="pb-20">Why Stumble?</h3>}
  <p>
    Stumble is on a mission to rekindle the art of old-fashioned conversation in a
    world where mindless swiping reigns supreme. As our motto strongly advocates,
    we yearn for a return to those simpler times when people would boldly strike
    up conversations with one anotherâ€”be it with a potential romantic interest or
    someone sporting a captivating t-shirt.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our generation has been raised on a diet of beloved romcoms like 'How I Met
    Your Mother' and 'F.R.I.E.N.D.S.' Yet, paradoxically, the majority of us opt
    for the convenience of social media apps and dating websites to seek out
    potential love interests, often located miles away.
  </p>
  <p>
    However, it's essential to acknowledge that we aren't solely responsible for
    this shift in social dynamics. Despite our exposure to these shows and a
    shared mindset, when we encounter someone we'd like to converse with, a
    multitude of apprehensions flood our minds, hindering us from approaching that
    enigmatic stranger.
  </p>
  <p>
    In the realm of potential romantic connections, these concerns may include:

    <ul>
      <li>What if that person isn't single?</li>
      <li>What if they're not actively seeking a relationship?</li>
      <li>What if their friends mock my approach?</li>
      <li>What if they're not attracted to my gender?</li>
      <li>
        What if, after approaching them, I discover they're not worth my time?
      </li>

      Similar inquiries may arise in other potential non-romantic encounters as
      well.
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>
    So, how do we surmount these obstacles and gain clarity on these questions
    before initiating contact? How can we dismantle the mental barriers that deter
    us from taking that first step? Well, these are precisely the conundrums we
    are dedicated to unraveling at Stumble.
  </p>
<div>

<style>
  .content {
		grid-column: 2 / 3;
		padding-bottom: 2vh;
	}

	.content p {
		margin-bottom: 50px;
	}

	.content ul {
		margin-bottom: 50px;
	}


	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

</style>